inline_comments.message:
why we are not involving the configuration here?
it seems reasonable to define the configuration properties with default values instead of constants.
it seems suitable for all the cases including testing and production,
should also resolve the sonar issue as well.

like in application.xml (same for tests)
```
security:
   auth:
      username: ${CPS_USERNAME:cpsuser}
      password: ${CPS_PASSWORD:cpsr0cks!}
```
then in code
```
@Value("${security.auth.username}")
private String username;

@Value("${security.auth.password}")
private String password;
```
